The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal processing, which are both covered by the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) sub-categories. The use of semidefinite programming also suggests that the paper may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper proposes a new formulation for atomic norm minimization, which is a numerical optimization technique, indicating that it may also be relevant to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category.
